		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Frederick Reiken</span></strong> is the author of three novels, most recently <em>Day for Night</em>, which was a finalist for the 2010 Los Angeles Times Book Prize in fiction. He lives with his wife and two daughters in western Massachusetts, where he&rsquo;s the coach of his five-year-old&rsquo;s soccer team. He teaches creative writing at Emerson College and will be the writer-in-residence at the Nether&shy;lands Institute for Advanced Study in 2014.</p><a href="/contributors/frederick-reiken" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
